The paper deals with regression problems in computer vision, specifically in the context of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach to regression using negative correlation learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between bias, variance, and covariance, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image super-resolution, which falls under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed method involves the use of an ensemble of deep networks, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE).
